text: Eugene N. Brodhagen (1917–1986) was an American football and wrestling coach. He served two stints as the head football coach at Winona State University in Winona, Minnesota from 1946 to 1950 and again from 1952 to 1954, compiling a record of 19–38–3. Brodhagen played college football at the University of Wisconsin, lettering from 1936 to 1938. ==Head coaching record== ===Football=== ==References== ==External links== * UW–Stevens Point Hall of Fame profile * Category:1917 births Category:1986 deaths Category:Wisconsin Badgers football players Category:Winona State Warriors football coaches Category:Wisconsin–Stevens Point Pointers football coaches Category:College wrestling coaches in the United States
